name: Foreshore Carpark toilets
directions: Only one cubicle marked gender neutral, but all stalls are single occupant.  Designated disabled parking bay right outside.
comment: There is lots of free untimed parking, including for caravans and RVs, but the area is VERY busy in summer.   Gender neutral  stall has wheelchair accessible toilet and basin,  sanitary disposal bin, rubbish bin,  change table and syringe disposal.   No soap.   All doors are manual with manual locks.

name: Foreshore Change rooms and Toilets
directions: Around back of  the building housing Equinox restaurant, facing away from the beach.   Wheelchair access via the footpath near the playground, and onto the verandah.   Open 24/7.
comment: Large gender neutral facility.  Includes toilet,  baby changing,  handwashing,  and shower with bench.  Rubbish bin and needle disposal, but no soap.   No parking within 100m, but lots of free untimed parking after that.   Would be a hassle to reach on wheels;  most direct route from parking only has stairs.  All stairs have rails.  All doors are manual with manual locks.

name: Busselton Visitors Centre
directions:
Through the Ballaarat Room.  Available when Visitors Centre is open, 9am - 5pm every day. 
More available outside, far end of building.   Open all the time.   

No baby change in outdoor toilets.
comment:
Lots of free off - road parking, but the area is VERY busy in summer and finding parking may be difficult. 

Designated disabled parking nearby,  ramps, kerb cutouts, stair rails and those bumpy stripes for low vision.  All toilet doors are  manual with manual locks.
